Clarke Leads Mickelson, Johnson by Three Shots in British Open Final Round

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-17T16:20:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/clarke-leads-mickelson-johnson-by-three-shots-in-british-open-final-round.html
Darren Clarke has extended his lead
to four shots in the final round of golf’s  British Open .  Clarke is 7-under par for the tournament at Royal St.
George’s in Sandwich,  England . The Northern Irishman is 2-under
par through 14 holes today.  Dustin Johnson , playing in the final group with Clarke,
made a double bogey at the par-5 14th hole to drop to 3-under,
tied with Denmark’s  Thomas Bjorn .  Phil Mickelson  was 6-under
after 10 holes, but has fallen back to 2-under.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  